The '''2008 Bank Austria-TennisTrophy''' was a [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Tennis court#Indoor courts|indoor hard courts]]. It was the 34th edition of the event known that year as the [[Bank Austria-TennisTrophy]], and was part of the [[ATP International Series Gold|International Series Gold]] of the [[2008 ATP Tour]]. It took place at the [[Wiener Stadthalle]] in [[Vienna]], Austria, from October 6 through October 12, 2008.

The singles featured [[Association of Tennis Professionals|ATP]] No. 10, [[2008 Rome Masters|Rome Masters]] and [[2008 Qatar ExxonMobil Open|Doha]] finalist, [[Tennis at the 2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing Olympics doubles gold medalist]] [[Stanislas Wawrinka]], [[Tennis at the 2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing Olympics silver medalist]], [[2008 Movistar Open|Vi<U+00F1>a del Mar]] and [[2008 BMW Open|Munich]] winner [[Fernando Gonz<U+00E1>lez]], and [[2008 Mercedes Cup|Stuttgart]], [[2008 Austrian Open (tennis)|Kitzb<U+00FC>hel]], [[2008 Countrywide Classic|Los Angeles]], [[2008 Legg Mason Tennis Classic|Washington]] champion, [[2008 AIG Japan Open Tennis Championships|Tokyo]] finalist [[Juan Mart<U+00ED>n del Potro]]. Also present were [[2008 Nottingham Open|Nottingham]] winner [[Ivo Karlovi<U+0107>]], [[2008 Croatia Open Umag|Umag]] titlist [[Fernando Verdasco]], [[Tommy Robredo]], [[Gilles Simon]] and [[Ga<U+00EB>l Monfils]].

